  * fm_manip.c (~6000 LOC under drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/sdk_fman/
  * Peripherals/FM/Pcd/ in the archived mihakralj/kernel-ls1046a-build
  * repo at HEAD 464df181) is a read-only silicon-fact cross-reference
- * only - no code or struct layouts are copied from it.  See spec
- * specs/ask2-rewrite-spec.md sec 16 (provenance discipline risk #12).
- *
- * What this file delivers at PR14d-prep
- * -------------------------------------
- * Two public entry points, both returning ERR_PTR(-EOPNOTSUPP) /
- * no-op.  No struct fman_pcd_manip definition yet - it stays forward-
- * declared in <linux/fsl/fman_pcd.h>.  No MURAM allocation, no register
