+ *
+ * Silicon facts driving the layout
+ * --------------------------------
+ *  - RM 8.7.5 paragraph 2: HMTD is a fixed 16-byte record (cross-ref
+ *    SDK fm_manip.h::t_Hmtd, 16 bytes).
+ *  - RM 8.7.5 paragraph 4: each HMCT command is a 4-byte word with
+ *    opcode bits[31:24] and operands in bits[23:0].  The list is
+ *    terminated by HMCD_LAST=0x00800000 OR'd into the last word.
+ *    Cross-ref SDK fm_manip.h::HMCD_*.
+ *  - RM 8.7.5.4: when bit HMCD_IP_L4_CS_CALC=0x00040000 is set in an
+ *    IPv4_UPDATE or IPv6_UPDATE HMCT command, the FMan re-computes
